#   SUBS-023: well-formed synthetic dot-branch `?/<sub>/.<parent>` won't resolve ‚Äî sub can't be re-attached by name (GRAFNONE)

A detached submodule should re-attach to its synthetic dot-branch by name ‚Äî
`be get '?/<sub>/.<parent>'` ‚Äî the canonical coordinate its commits live on. But
that query won't RESOLVE: `be head '?/abc/.dogs'` (the get dry-run) returns
`graf: head: cannot resolve target` / GRAFNONE at both the parent and the recursed
sub level, even though the abc shard's refs DO carry `?/abc/.dogs#<sha>`. So a
detached sub cannot be re-attached to its dot-branch by name. Flagged as a
[SUBS-021] follow-up; confirmed 2026-06-16. Research ‚Üí fix. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Repro (`~/beagle`, read-only dry-run): `be head '?/abc/.dogs'` ‚Üí
    `graf: head: cannot resolve target` / `Error: GRAFNONE` (twice ‚Äî it recurses
    `be: head .` / `be: head abc` and both miss). Same with a `#<sha>` fragment.
 -  Yet the abc sub-shard's refs hold the dot-branch tip, e.g.
    `~/beagle/.be/abc/refs`: `26616Bkc1V  post  ?/abc/.dogs#02a23dc3‚Ä¶` ‚Äî the branch
    EXISTS, the resolver just can't map the `?/<sub>/.<parent>` query to it.
 -  Background: a detached sub tip is `?<sha>` and its commits sit on the synthetic
    coordinate `?/<sub>/.<parent>` (see [submodule-synthetic-branch-post],
    [submodule-tip-detached-form]). The POST composer writes that branch correctly;
    GET/HEAD resolution of it is the gap.

### Goals
 -  `be get '?/<sub>/.<parent>'` (and `be head`) RESOLVES the synthetic dot-branch to
    its tip and re-attaches the sub there ‚Äî symmetric with how POST writes it.
 -  Works at the sub level and via parent recursion; a `#<sha>` fragment pins the cur.

### Constraints
 -  Resolve through the existing REFS/synthetic-branch machinery
    (`sniff/GET.c` synth/`DOGQueryStripProject` path ~`:1910-1999`; graf head's
    `GRAFResolveTip`/`REFSResolve`); do NOT re-roll branch parsing. No new flags.

