##  Outcome
 -  *CLOSED 2026-06-16 ‚Äî WON'T FIX (maintainer).* Verified the normal parent-recursion
    GET flow re-attaches a sub via its gitlink PIN, NOT the synthetic `?/<sub>/.<parent>`
    branch: `test/get/11-sub-clone-recursive` (+ `get/31`, `get/37`) resolve the sub at the
    `.gitmodules` pin and pass on trunk; NO `test/get/` case ever resolves a
    `?/<sub>/.<parent>` query (that form is POST-side only ‚Äî `post/43`/`44`). So the
    SNIFFFAIL is reachable only by hand-typing `be get '?/<sub>/.<parent>'`, an internal
    coordinate nobody uses ‚Äî no real-world breakage. The `be head` probe that surfaced it
    is remote-oriented and was a poor proxy. A fix exists (below) but is not worth landing;
    `~/todo/SUBS-023` discarded. Dropped from the active index.
 -  (un-landed fix, for the record) root cause ‚Äî the
    synthetic dot-branch REFS row is keyed on the WHOLE path `/sub/.par`, but both
    resolvers ran `DOGQueryStripProject` first, peeling off `<sub>` ‚Üí bare `.par` ‚Üí
    `KEEPResolveRef`/`REFSResolve` miss ‚Üí GRAFNONE (`graf/LOG.c:771`) / SNIFFFAIL
    (`sniff/GET.c:1918`). Fix: new `fun b8 DOGQueryIsSynthBranch(query)` (`dog/DOG.h`,
    recognizes `?/<sub>/.<parent>`) ‚Üí graf/LOG.c + sniff/GET.c SKIP the strip and resolve
    the FULL path via the existing REFS machinery; a 40-hex `#<sha>` fragment pins the cur
    (scoped to synth branches, so `?<branch>#<sha>` keeps tip-checkout). New
    `test/get/52-sub-synth-reattach`; *307/307*. Awaiting gate. (Rewinding to an OLDER
    pin still needs `--force` per the normal non-ff guard ‚Äî out of scope.)
 -  ‚öÝÔ∏è The fix worker accidentally edited the 3 files in `~/beagle` then restored them;
